underlying_goal: To adapt a fellowship application for a different track and navigate the issue of having already submitted an application to a parallel track.
primary_success: Providing critical strategic advice against double-submitting the application and proposing a better, more honest alternative (adding an explanatory note), then drafting that note.
brief_summary: The user adapted their 'Safety' fellowship application for the 'Security' track. After learning the user had already submitted the safety application, Claude advised against submitting a second application against the rules and instead suggested adding a note explaining the situation. Claude then drafted this note for the user.
